WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.928 align:middle line:90%
[WHOOSH]

00:00:03.928 --> 00:00:11.784 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.784 --> 00:00:15.250 align:middle line:90%
[CHILDREN PLAYING]

00:00:15.250 --> 00:00:17.770 align:middle line:84%
>> When we are kids, we say
that one day we'll explore

00:00:17.770 --> 00:00:19.120 align:middle line:90%
the world.

00:00:19.120 --> 00:00:21.460 align:middle line:84%
Then we grow up,
routine sets in,

00:00:21.460 --> 00:00:24.010 align:middle line:84%
and we forget about
those childhood dreams.

00:00:24.010 --> 00:00:26.380 align:middle line:84%
But for some reason,
something compelled a friend

00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:28.240 align:middle line:90%
and I to follow this dream.

00:00:28.240 --> 00:00:30.504 align:middle line:90%
This is our story.

00:00:30.504 --> 00:00:38.800 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:38.800 --> 00:00:41.950 align:middle line:84%
>> That summer, I went to
visit Marc in New York.

00:00:41.950 --> 00:00:43.850 align:middle line:84%
We had not seen each
other in 10 years,

00:00:43.850 --> 00:00:47.200 align:middle line:84%
and at first it was like we
had nothing left in common.

00:00:47.200 --> 00:00:49.880 align:middle line:84%
I had just finished a movie
on water access in India,

00:00:49.880 --> 00:00:52.000 align:middle line:84%
and he was working
in marketing, trying

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:55.240 align:middle line:84%
to convince Americans that
bottled water was a luxury

00:00:55.240 --> 00:00:57.640 align:middle line:90%
product.

00:00:57.640 --> 00:01:01.030 align:middle line:84%
But we ended up hitting it
off like in the good old days,

00:01:01.030 --> 00:01:03.280 align:middle line:84%
when we used to play in his
grandmother's backyard .

00:01:03.280 --> 00:01:06.015 align:middle line:84%
But this time our
playground was Central Park.

00:01:06.015 --> 00:01:10.110 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:10.110 --> 00:01:13.290 align:middle line:84%
>> In New York, we were living
the high life in between

00:01:13.290 --> 00:01:15.840 align:middle line:84%
the high end restaurants,
the VIP clubs,

00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:17.970 align:middle line:84%
and the apartment
right on Wall Street.

00:01:17.970 --> 00:01:20.310 align:middle line:84%
Marc was living the
American dream--

00:01:20.310 --> 00:01:23.610 align:middle line:84%
the one everyone on
the planet dreams of.

00:01:23.610 --> 00:01:25.560 align:middle line:84%
But I felt he was
a bit out of place

00:01:25.560 --> 00:01:26.790 align:middle line:90%
in this superficial world.

00:01:26.790 --> 00:01:29.310 align:middle line:90%


00:01:29.310 --> 00:01:32.010 align:middle line:84%
So before leaving,
I left him a pile

00:01:32.010 --> 00:01:35.040 align:middle line:84%
of documentaries to shake him
up a bit and get him thinking.

00:01:35.040 --> 00:01:40.120 align:middle line:90%


00:01:40.120 --> 00:01:43.490 align:middle line:84%
- Me, I was perfectly happy
in my little Manhattan bubble.

00:01:43.490 --> 00:01:45.500 align:middle line:84%
I had landed a job
of my dreams, and I

00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:47.900 align:middle line:84%
had no intention
whatsoever of watching

00:01:47.900 --> 00:01:49.610 align:middle line:90%
Nathanael's documentaries.

00:01:49.610 --> 00:01:51.680 align:middle line:84%
But that's when life
called me to order.

00:01:51.680 --> 00:01:53.750 align:middle line:84%
One day when I was
pretending to be

00:01:53.750 --> 00:01:56.570 align:middle line:84%
Michael Jordan in my hallway,
I slipped on the ball

00:01:56.570 --> 00:01:57.890 align:middle line:90%
and broke my foot.

00:01:57.890 --> 00:01:59.570 align:middle line:84%
As I was stuck in
bed, I ended up

00:01:59.570 --> 00:02:01.140 align:middle line:84%
watching all those
documentaries.

00:02:01.140 --> 00:02:05.084 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:05.084 --> 00:02:25.300 align:middle line:90%


00:02:25.300 --> 00:02:28.280 align:middle line:84%
>> After that, I've got to
say, it was hard to get back

00:02:28.280 --> 00:02:30.910 align:middle line:90%
to work.

00:02:30.910 --> 00:02:32.880 align:middle line:84%
Especially since
at the same moment,

00:02:32.880 --> 00:02:34.810 align:middle line:90%
the financial crisis hit.

00:02:34.810 --> 00:02:36.700 align:middle line:84%
