violence, war, climate change--

00:53:57.620 --> 00:54:01.115 align:middle line:84%
they spring from the
way we view the world.

00:54:01.115 --> 00:54:07.980 align:middle line:90%


00:54:07.980 --> 00:54:09.810 align:middle line:84%
One of the projects
we're working

00:54:09.810 --> 00:54:12.210 align:middle line:84%
on here at the Institute
of Noetic Sciences

00:54:12.210 --> 00:54:14.760 align:middle line:84%
is called Worldview
Literacy, where

00:54:14.760 --> 00:54:18.810 align:middle line:84%
we're helping people see
how they view everything

00:54:18.810 --> 00:54:20.910 align:middle line:90%
through a worldview.

00:54:20.910 --> 00:54:22.470 align:middle line:84%
It's almost as though
they're looking

00:54:22.470 --> 00:54:24.450 align:middle line:90%
through a pair of glasses.

00:54:24.450 --> 00:54:29.430 align:middle line:84%
And their worldview
arises from many factors--

00:54:29.430 --> 00:54:34.330 align:middle line:84%
genetics, culture, religion,
how they were raised,

00:54:34.330 --> 00:54:36.570 align:middle line:84%
what they've learned in
school, the experiences

00:54:36.570 --> 00:54:38.410 align:middle line:90%
they've had in their lives.

00:54:38.410 --> 00:54:43.230 align:middle line:84%
And most of us are not aware of
the worldviews we're holding.

00:54:43.230 --> 00:54:46.450 align:middle line:90%
